<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-12-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-12-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="867" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d867">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Ambassador <persName type="to">Meyer</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-12-13"><hi rend="italic">December 13,
                                    1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Root instructs Mr. Meyer to ascertain whether necessary instructions
                            for the surrender of the Japanese prisoners held in Manchuria have been
                            issued to the Russian military authorities.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>